io.confluent.ksql.execution.interpreter.terms

Interface Term

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ArithmeticBinaryTerm, ArithmeticUnaryTerm, CastTerm, ColumnReferenceTerm, ComparisonTerm.CompareToTerm, ComparisonTerm.EqualsTerm, CreateArrayTerm, CreateMapTerm, DereferenceTerm, FunctionCallTerm, InPredicateTerm, IsNotNullTerm, IsNullTerm, LambdaFunctionTerms.LambdaFunction1Term, LambdaFunctionTerms.LambdaFunction2Term, LambdaFunctionTerms.LambdaFunction3Term, LambdaFunctionTerms.LambdaFunctionBaseTerm, LambdaVariableTerm, LikeTerm, LiteralTerms.BooleanTermImpl, LiteralTerms.BytesTermImpl, LiteralTerms.DateTermImpl, LiteralTerms.DecimalTermImpl, LiteralTerms.DoubleTermImpl, LiteralTerms.IntegerTermImpl, LiteralTerms.IntervalUnitTermImpl, LiteralTerms.LongTermImpl, LiteralTerms.NullTerm, LiteralTerms.StringTermImpl, LiteralTerms.TimestampTermImpl, LiteralTerms.TimeTermImpl, LogicalBinaryTerms.AndTerm, LogicalBinaryTerms.OrTerm, NotTerm, SearchedCaseTerm, StructTerm, SubscriptTerm

    public interface Term
    The "compiled" state for an InterpretedExpression that contains all information about the underlying expression necessary to evaluate it, without knowing the input row(s) on which it will be invoked. Terms are meant to be reused across many row evaluations and should therefore hold no row-based state. They are created directly from TermCompiler and involve no java code generation, hence being interpreted.
